# Deployment Workflow - Simple but Scalable

Progressive deployment strategy with preview environments, automated staging, and gated production releases for Freshworks apps and services.

**Justification:** Safe, incremental deployments reduce risk, enable rapid iteration, and maintain production stability for enterprise CRM integrations.

## 🚀 Deployment Flow Overview

```mermaid
graph LR
    PR[Pull Request] --> Preview[Preview URL]
    Preview --> Smoke[E2E Smoke Tests]
    Smoke --> Merge[Merge to Main]
    Merge --> Staging[Auto-Deploy Staging]
    Staging --> StagingTests[Post-Deploy Tests]
    StagingTests --> Approve{Manual Approve?}
    Approve -->|Yes| Prod[Production Deploy]
    Approve -->|Auto| ProdAuto[Auto-Promote if Green]
    Prod --> ProdTests[Production Smoke Tests]
    ProdTests --> Notify[Notify Team]
```

## 📦 Phase 1: Preview Deployments (Per PR)

**Purpose:** Test changes in isolation before merging

### Freshworks Apps (FDK)
```bash
# Local preview for Freshworks apps
cd apps/freshsales-intake-guard
pnpm fdk run --tunnel  # Creates temporary public URL

# Automated in CI
on:
  pull_request:
    paths:
      - 'apps/freshsales-*/**'
jobs:
  preview:
    steps:
      - run: pnpm nx build freshsales-intake-guard
      - run: pnpm fdk validate
      - run: pnpm fdk pack
      - comment: "Preview URL: https://pr-${{ github.event.number }}.preview.freshworks.dev"
```

### Web Services (Vercel/Netlify)
```yaml
# Automatic preview deployments
# vercel.json or netlify.toml
{
  "github": {
    "enabled": true,
    "autoAlias": ["pr-*.preview.example.com"]
  }
}
```

### AWS Services (CDK)
```bash
# Ephemeral stack per PR
./scripts/deploy-webhook-stack.sh up \
  --name "pr-${PR_NUMBER}-webhook" \
  --region us-east-1 \
  --profile dev

# Auto-cleanup after merge
./scripts/deploy-webhook-stack.sh down \
  --name "pr-${PR_NUMBER}-webhook"
```

### E2E Tests Against Preview
```typescript
// tests/e2e/smoke.test.ts
const PREVIEW_URL = process.env.PREVIEW_URL || 'http://localhost:3000';

describe('Preview Smoke Tests', () => {
  it('should have working health endpoint', async () => {
    const res = await fetch(`${PREVIEW_URL}/healthz`);
    expect(res.ok).toBe(true);
  });
  
  it('should handle webhook requests', async () => {
    const res = await fetch(`${PREVIEW_URL}/eleven/personalize`, {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ freshsales_contact_id: 123 })
    });
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
  });
});
```

## 🎯 Phase 2: Staging Deployment (Main Branch)

**Purpose:** Integration testing in production-like environment

### Auto-Deploy on Merge
```yaml
# .github/workflows/deploy-staging.yml
name: Deploy to Staging
on:
  push:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  deploy-staging:
    environment: staging
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - uses: pnpm/action-setup@v2
      
      # Deploy affected services
      - run: pnpm nx affected -t deploy --stage=staging
      
      # Deploy CDK stacks
      - run: |
          cd apps/infra/eleven-webhook-cdk
          npx cdk deploy --context stage=staging --require-approval never
      
      # Deploy Freshworks apps
      - run: |
          cd apps/freshsales-intake-guard
          pnpm fdk pack
          curl -X POST ${{ secrets.FRESHWORKS_STAGING_API }}/apps \
            -F "app=@dist/freshsales-intake-guard.zip"
```

### Post-Deploy Validation
```bash
# Run smoke tests against staging
pnpm test:e2e:staging

# Health checks
curl -f https://staging.api.example.com/healthz
curl -f https://staging.webhook.example.com/healthz

# Synthetic monitoring
aws synthetics start-canary --name staging-smoke-tests
```

