### Notifications
```bash
# scripts/notify-deployment.sh
#!/bin/bash
WEBHOOK_URL="${SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL}"
STATUS="${1:-success}"
ENV="${2:-production}"
VERSION="${3:-unknown}"

curl -X POST "${WEBHOOK_URL}" \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d @- <<EOF
{
  "text": "🚀 Deployment to ${ENV}",
  "attachments": [{
    "color": "${STATUS}" == "success" ? "good" : "danger",
    "fields": [
      {"title": "Environment", "value": "${ENV}", "short": true},
      {"title": "Version", "value": "${VERSION}", "short": true},
      {"title": "Status", "value": "${STATUS}", "short": true},
      {"title": "Dashboard", "value": "<https://dashboard.example.com|View Metrics>"}
    ]
  }]
}
EOF
```

## 🛡️ Rollback Strategy

### Instant Rollback
```bash
# Freshworks Apps
curl -X POST $FRESHWORKS_API/apps/$APP_ID/rollback \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $API_KEY"

# AWS Services (Blue-Green)
aws elbv2 modify-listener \
  --listener-arn $PROD_LISTENER_ARN \
  --default-actions Type=forward,TargetGroupArn=$BLUE_TG_ARN

# Vercel/Netlify
vercel rollback production --yes
```

### Monitoring & Alerts
```yaml
# Datadog/CloudWatch alerts
alerts:
  - name: deployment-error-rate
    query: "avg(last_5m):error_rate > 0.05"
    action: 
      - notify: "@oncall"
      - trigger: "rollback-automation"
  
  - name: deployment-latency
    query: "avg(last_5m):p95_latency > 1000"
    action:
      - notify: "@team"
      - suggest: "rollback"
```

## 📊 Success Metrics

- **Preview Deployments:** Created within 2 minutes of PR
- **Staging Deploy:** Completes within 5 minutes of merge
- **Production Deploy:** Zero-downtime, < 10 minute total time
- **Rollback Time:** < 30 seconds to revert
- **Test Coverage:** 100% critical paths covered by smoke tests
- **Alert Response:** < 2 minutes to detect production issues
